---
title: Greek Hamburger Pita Pockets with Cucumber-Tomato Salad, Garlicky White Sauce & Feta
description: This hearty meal is packed with fresh, savory Mediterranean-style flavors. You'll load juicy seasoned ground beef into warm pita pockets spread with tangy garlic-yogurt sauce and top with juicy tomato-cucumber salad and crumbled feta cheese. Serve with more salad on the side for a mouthwatering meal in a speedy 20 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6716a6b7ffa4e28ccb95eb53-bd747c70.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6716a6b7ffa4e28ccb95eb53-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 730 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 46 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1020 mg
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/greek-hamburger-pita-pockets-6716a6b7ffa4e28ccb95eb53
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan
over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounces}, half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and
@pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Carefully drain any excess grease
from pan.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into 1/4-inch-thick pieces. Dice @tomato{1} into 1/4-inch pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoons} and remaining
@garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}. Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, a
drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm
and pliable, ~{30-40%seconds}. Halve pitas; gently pull apart
to create pockets.

> Halve pitas one at a time to make opening easier and prevent them from sticking. You can also toast them for added texture!

Spread insides of each pita pocket with as much sauce
as you like, then fill with beef and salad. Drizzle any
remaining sauce on top. Serve with any remaining salad
on the side.

> If you like things spicy, add a drizzle of your favorite hot sauce!

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.